\intbl \ql \b Summary of Evaluator Report\b0 \line The evaluator indicated that the programme meets the minimum requirements for most of the criteria and recommended that the programme be accredited with conditions. However\'2C he\'2Fshe commented on and questions the omission of Criteria 3 \'26 4 \'28Staffing\'29\'2C as well as Criteria  7 \'26 8 \'28Infrastructure\'2C resources and programme administrative services\'29. It should be noted that public institutions sign a declaration and are not required to provide information on staffing \'28Criteria 3 \'26 4\'29 or infrastructure and systems \'28Criterion 7 \'26 8\'29.\line \line The purpose and rationale of the programme are clear and are focused on the development of the candidates\'27 theoretical and pedagogical knowledge of the four \'27dominant\'27 languages that are spoken in the Northern Cape\'2C i.e. Afrikaans\'2C English\'2C isiXhosa and Setswana. Students will complete the three theoretical modules\'2C i.e. Philosophy of Language\'2C Language Methodology \'28with a choice of Afrikaans\'2C English\'2C isiXhosa or Setswana\'29\'2C Literature Methodology \'28a choice between the four local languages\'29\'2C and finally complete the module\'2C \'27Research in Language Education\'27 \'28supervised research based on the three foregoing modules\'29. The evaluator indicated that the documentation outlines the modules clearly and provides a detailed breakdown of the module outcomes\'2C the assessment criteria\'2C the unit content and the prescribed reading. \line \line The Institution submitted a module descriptor for each of the modules\'2C including the literature methodology and language methodology for each of the four languages. The evaluator noted that the Institution omitted the module descriptor for Setswana Language Methodology. Also\'2C he\'2Fshe mentioned that no module documentation is available for Afrikaans\'2C English and isiXhosa Literature Methodology. The Directorate agrees that all the module descriptors were submitted\'2C however\'2C the module outline for Setswana Literature was erroneously titled\'2C Afrikaans Literature Methodology.\line \line The students are required to conduct research under supervision. The research report or essay will be submitted for assessment. Although the Institution requires that students conduct research\'2C the programmes does not include a module that introduces students to research methodology. The module descriptor for the research module does not refer to any training in methodology. It seems as if students are required to conduct research without a proper introduction to research methodology. Furthermore\'2C this raises questions in terms of articulation and students\'27 readiness for Master\'27s studies. The Institution claims that the PGDip \'28Language Education\'29 provides for articulation into cognate Master\'27s programmes. The Institution needs to clarify the research and methodology components of this programme and verify whether this programme prepares students for Master\'27s studies.\line \line The student admission and selection criteria adhere to current national legislation and are commensurate with the programme\'27s academic requirements. The Recognition of Prior Learning \'28RPL\'29 is permitted and the assessment thereof is aligned with the University\'27s RPL Policy.  \line \line As this is a public institution\'2C Criteria 3\'2C 4\'2C 7 and 8 are deemed to be in place.\line \line The Teaching and Learning Strategy is relevant to the contact mode of delivery of the programme\'2C and seek to utilise varied innovative programme delivery methods and strategies\'2C such as engaged learning\'2C collaborative learning\'2C experience-based learning\'2C problem-based learning\'2C reflective learning\'2C community service learning\'2C resource-based learning\'2C E-learning\'2C group work and directed self-study\'2C which serve to advance lifelong deep learning. The Directorate for Teaching\'2C Learning and Curriculum development provides academic support to students and aims to deepen the students\'27 postgraduate experience.\line \line The evaluator indicated that the Assessment Strategy is appropriate to the teaching and learning methods in this programme. Assessment practices are subject to the institutional Assessment Policy. The Institution explained that the programme will be evaluated through continuous and summative assessments. Continuous assessment will take place during the course of the theoretical modules\'2C including assignments\'2C case studies and class tests. Summative assessments comprise of examinations at the end of each theoretical module. The research essay will be subject to a summative assessment only. The Institution confirmed that moderation will be done both internally and externally.\line \line The PGDip \'28Language Education\'29 requires that students conduct research under supervision and submit a written research report\'2Fessay. However\'2C the Institution omitted Criterion 9 and did not provide any evidence related to the research component of the programme\'2C i.e. supervision\'2C selection of students\'2C roles and responsibilities of supervisors and students\'2C research outputs\'2C research policies and guidelines\'2C etc. The evaluator could therefore not determine whether the Institution has the appropriate policies\'2C procedures and regulations\'2C as well as the research capacity to offer and support the programme.  This information must be provided.\line \line The Directorate recommends that the programme be accredited with conditions.\cell \pard 

